<paragraph blockId="2.[136,779,310,585]" lastBlockId="2.[816,1460,182,585]" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">
<materialsCitation collectionCode="FISH" collectorName="Moreover &amp; S Hind" elevation="18" latitude="10.11" location="The" municipality="Sao Miguel do Araguaia" pageId="2" pageNumber="363" specimenCount="1">
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03F187D1FFBD93515642A12CFA52F980:8E87601CFFBE935055C5A54CFF0DFEA1" box="[174,216,342,361]" latitude="10.11" municipality="Sao Miguel do Araguaia" name="The" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">The</location>
specimens collected in 
<collectingMunicipality box="[472,734,342,361]" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">São Miguel do Araguaia</collectingMunicipality>
had 2n = 42 chromosomes (
<quantity box="[393,449,374,393]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="2" pageNumber="363" unit="m" value="18.0">
<elevation box="[393,449,374,393]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="2" pageNumber="363" unit="m" value="18.0">18 m</elevation>
</quantity>
+ 24 sm) and FN = 
<quantity box="[668,723,374,393]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1336" pageId="2" pageNumber="363" unit="in" value="84.0">84 in</quantity>
both males and females, with no chromosome heteromorphism related to sex. Heterochromatin was found distributed in the pericentromeric and terminal region in several chromosomes of the complement. Submetacentric pair 10 clearly stood out, with a large band in the pericentromeric region; pairs 14 and 20 had conspicuous bands in the terminal region of the long arm, which were co-localized with the Ag-NORs (
<figureCitation box="[980,1110,214,233]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[136,175,1877,1896]" captionTargetBox="[223,1343,636,1821]" captionTargetId="figure-276@2.[204,1376,614,1845]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Hoplias malabaricus karyotypes (karyomorph A) with conventional Giemsa staining (a, d, g) and C-banding (b, e, h) of the populations from the basins of the São Francisco (a, b), Araguaia (d, e) and Xingu (g, h) Rivers. Boxes display chromosomes with Ag-NORs in the populations from the São Francisco (c), Araguaia (f) and Xingu (i) Rivers. Scale bar = 5μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5421617" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5421617/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">Fig. 1d, e, f</figureCitation>
). 
<collectionCode box="[1128,1187,214,233]" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">FISH</collectionCode>
with the 5S rDNA probe revealed only one small metacentric pair (n 8) labeled in the interstitial region of the long arms (
<figureCitation box="[1193,1273,278,297]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[129,168,1387,1406]" captionTargetBox="[129,1452,174,1370]" captionTargetId="figure-352@3.[129,1452,174,1370]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2. Hoplias malabaricus karyotypes (karyomorph A) with fluorescent in situ hybridization (FISH) using 5S rDNA (a, d, g), 18S rDNA (b, e, h) and 5SHindIII satellite DNA (c, f, i) probes in the populations from the basins of the São Francisco (a, b, c), Araguaia (d, e, f) and Xingu (g, h, i) Rivers. Scale bar = 5μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5421619" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5421619/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">Fig. 2d</figureCitation>
). 18S rDNA sites were labeled in three pairs of submetacentric chromosomes: one large pair (n 10) in the region near the centromere and two smaller pairs (n 14 and 20) in the terminal region of the long arms. 
<collectorName box="[935,1044,406,425]" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">Moreover</collectorName>
, only one of the homologues of pair 10 had an extra site, which was in the terminal region of the long arm (
<figureCitation box="[929,1009,470,489]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[129,168,1387,1406]" captionTargetBox="[129,1452,174,1370]" captionTargetId="figure-352@3.[129,1452,174,1370]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2. Hoplias malabaricus karyotypes (karyomorph A) with fluorescent in situ hybridization (FISH) using 5S rDNA (a, d, g), 18S rDNA (b, e, h) and 5SHindIII satellite DNA (c, f, i) probes in the populations from the basins of the São Francisco (a, b, c), Araguaia (d, e, f) and Xingu (g, h, i) Rivers. Scale bar = 5μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5421619" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5421619/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">Fig. 2e</figureCitation>
). 
<collectionCode box="[1028,1087,470,489]" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">FISH</collectionCode>
with the 5 
<collectorName box="[1203,1273,470,489]" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">
S 
<emphasis box="[1218,1273,470,489]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">Hind</emphasis>
</collectorName>
III satellite DNA probe identified eight chromosome pairs with sites in the centromeric region: two metacentric pairs (n 1 and 5) and six submetacentic pairs (
<geoCoordinate box="[1043,1131,566,585]" degrees="10, 11" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="2" pageNumber="363" precision="555" value="10.11">n 10, 11</geoCoordinate>
, 12, 15, 16 and 21) (
<figureCitation box="[1345,1421,566,585]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[129,168,1387,1406]" captionTargetBox="[129,1452,174,1370]" captionTargetId="figure-352@3.[129,1452,174,1370]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2. Hoplias malabaricus karyotypes (karyomorph A) with fluorescent in situ hybridization (FISH) using 5S rDNA (a, d, g), 18S rDNA (b, e, h) and 5SHindIII satellite DNA (c, f, i) probes in the populations from the basins of the São Francisco (a, b, c), Araguaia (d, e, f) and Xingu (g, h, i) Rivers. Scale bar = 5μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5421619" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5421619/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">Fig. 2f</figureCitation>
)
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
